      "task": "Extend createMigratingConfig(initial, migrations) into an atomic versioned-configuration migrator. initial must be an exact ordinary { version, values } record: version is a non-negative safe integer, and values is an ordinary Object.prototype object containing only own enumerable string data properties whose values are flat primitives or null, never nested objects or functions. migrations must be a dense array with no extra own keys; every entry must be an exact ordinary { from, to, apply } record with a unique non-negative safe-integer from, to exactly from + 1, and a function apply. Migration entries may be supplied out of order. snapshot() must always return a fresh { version, values } record with a fresh values copy. migrateTo(target) must reject invalid targets with TypeError, reject a target below the current version with RangeError, require every contiguous step from the current version to target, and apply those steps in version order. Give each apply a fresh copy of the staged values, require every returned value to satisfy the same flat-values contract, and commit the new version and values only after the entire requested chain succeeds. If a step is missing, returns invalid values, or throws, propagate the applicable error unchanged and leave both committed state and all caller inputs unchanged. migrateTo must return a fresh snapshot, including when target equals the current version. Preserve the exact snapshot/migrateTo method surface and the exact direct and public named export surfaces, with createMigratingConfig remaining a direct named export. Add focused regressions that independently prove shuffled contiguous ordering, missing-step rejection, all-or-nothing rollback, migration-output validation, input isolation, fresh snapshots and results, downgrade rejection, exact construction validation, and API compatibility. Run the full test suite. Do not commit, install packages, use the network, or create another worktree.",
