      "task": "Extend mergeStablePriorityItems(lanes) so lanes is a dense array of dense arrays of exact ordinary records with exactly the own data properties { id, priority, value }. id must be a non-empty primitive string, priority must be any safe integer, and value may be any value. Treat the outer lane order and then each lane's item order as the global encounter order. Return one winner per id: the record with the highest priority wins, and equal-priority duplicates keep the earliest encounter. Sort winners by descending priority and preserve the winning records' encounter order when priorities tie, including when a later encounter promoted an id over an earlier lower-priority record. Never mutate the outer array, lanes, or input records. Return a dense array of fresh exact { id, priority, value } records while preserving each winning value reference. Reject sparse arrays, inherited or extra fields, accessors, symbol keys, non-ordinary records, invalid ids, and non-safe-integer priorities with TypeError. Preserve the exact direct and public named export surfaces, and keep mergeStablePriorityItems as a direct named export. Add focused regressions that independently prove global descending priority, stable winner ordering, highest-priority duplicate selection, earliest equal-priority duplicate selection, dense exact-record validation, input immutability, fresh output records, safe-integer boundaries, arbitrary values, and export compatibility. Run the full test suite. Do not commit, install packages, use the network, or create another worktree.",
